[normal]  In  view of these difficulties, it is hardly surprising that of the 658 Torbay residents who commute to Plymouth
[normal] for their work
[normal], only 23 do so by train
[normal];  518 travel by car,
[normal] 27 as passengers in a car
[normal] and 26 by bus;
[normal] the bus takes two hours, as against a possible 55 minutes by train if only there were a direct train.
[normal]  
[normal]Of the 487 who commute from Plymouth to Torbay, only three do so by train; 
[normal] 
[normal]376 commute by car, 23 as passenger
[normal]s,  six by bus and 
[normal]eight
[normal] by motorcycle.
[normal]15.  Trains to Gunnislake
[normal] (the Tamar Valley line)
