[normal]17
[normal].
[normal]  Exmouth enjoys a half-hourly service to Exeter Central and Exeter St Davids.  This is made up of the roughly hourly service from Paignton 
[normal] to Exmouth 
[normal]and the hourly direct service 
[normal]from Barnstaple (the Tarka line)
[normal] to  Exmouth
[normal].  
[normal]Torbay
[normal] has twice the population of Exmouth and Barnstaple put together.  Surely Paignton should have at least a h
[normal]alf-hourly local service to the centre of Exeter.  Both the Exmouth and the Barnstaple lines are
[normal] 
[normal]very successful and extremely well used.  Figures given by First Great Western
[normal] showed that journeys on the Exmouth (Avocet) line numbered 1.4million in 2012 and had increased by 10% and on the Barnstaple line by 78% since 2006.  A more frequent service f
[normal]rom Barnstaple could help fill the gaps in the timetable between Paignton  and Exeter St Davids and between Torbay and Plymouth.
[normal]1
[normal]8
[normal]. 
